# Next.js Frontend

## Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router
- TypeScript strict
- Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- TanStack Query + `useInfiniteQuery` for marketplace catalog
- `@tanstack/react-virtual` for 100+ product grids
- React Hook Form + Zod

## Structure

```
src/app/          # Routes (App Router)
src/components/   # UI components
src/lib/api/      # API client functions (call gateway)
```

## Rules

- Follow `ui-design.mdc` for all UI work
- No product business logic in platform repos
- Auth via OIDC — no custom token storage in localStorage
- API calls go through gateway URLs, not direct product backend origins
- Keep components small; colocate hooks when used once
- Platform UI lives in `platform-frontend` (dashboard + marketplace routes)

## Simplicity

- Prefer server components where data is read-only
- Client components only when interactivity is needed
- No premature abstraction — see `simple-code.mdc`
